\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Universal collapse of binding energy curves. Left (a--c): Morse potentials with diverse well depths and equilibrium distances collapse onto the universal Rose/UBER form $E/E_c$ versus $a^* = (r-r_e)/l$. Right (d--f): Lennard-Jones potentials collapse by construction onto $V/\varepsilon $ versus $r/\sigma $. The scaling parameters vary smoothly with descriptors, making them natural regression targets.}}{3}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:collapse}{{2}{3}{Universal collapse of binding energy curves. Left (a--c): Morse potentials with diverse well depths and equilibrium distances collapse onto the universal Rose/UBER form $E/E_c$ versus $a^* = (r-r_e)/l$. Right (d--f): Lennard-Jones potentials collapse by construction onto $V/\varepsilon $ versus $r/\sigma $. The scaling parameters vary smoothly with descriptors, making them natural regression targets}{figure.2}{}}
